# CI/CD Project Notes

## Project Goal
Build a continuous delivery pipeline that automatically deploys a Node.js application to AWS Elastic Beanstalk when code is pushed to GitHub.

## Architecture
GitHub → AWS CodePipeline → AWS CodeBuild → Manual Approval → AWS Elastic Beanstalk

## Key AWS Services Used
- AWS CodePipeline (orchestration)
- AWS CodeBuild (build & test automation)
- AWS Elastic Beanstalk (application hosting)
- IAM (service role permissions)
- S3 (artifact storage)

## Implementation Steps
1. Created Node.js sample application.
2. Added buildspec.yml for automated builds.
3. Configured CodePipeline with GitHub source.
4. Connected CodeBuild project.
5. Added Manual Approval stage.
6. Configured Elastic Beanstalk deploy stage.
7. Fixed IAM permission issue for CreateApplicationVersion.

## Challenges Faced
- IAM permission error: elasticbeanstalk:CreateApplicationVersion missing.
- Resolved by attaching Elastic Beanstalk permissions to CodePipeline role.
